<section id="eip-334"><title>Saturation region</title><para id="eip-599">This is the region where the JFET is completely “ON”. The maximum amount of current is flowing for the given gate-source voltage. In this region the drain current can be modeled by the <link target-id="eip-284"/> , where I<sub>D</sub> is the drain current, I<sub>DSS</sub> is the maximum current, V<sub>GS</sub> is the gate-source voltage, and V<sub>P</sub> is the pinch off voltage. Solving for the pinch off voltage results in <link target-id="eip-823"/>.
</para>


