<section id="eip-981"><title>Pinch-off  region (cutoff region)</title><para id="eip-949">When the gate-source voltage, V<sub>GS</sub>,  is below the threshold voltage V<sub>T </sub> the charge carriers in the channel are not available “cutting off” the charge flow. Power dissipation for MOSFETs can also be solved using equation 6 in any region as in the JFET case. 
</para></section></section><section id="import-auto-id1165516391848">
